cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on energy consumption in cellular networks, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses closed form expressions to evaluate the mean and variance of the consumed energy, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses power control and battery dimensioning, which are related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the broadcast part of energy, which is related to multimedia broadcasting. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, energy consumption is also a concern in cryptography and security, especially in resource-constrained devices.
